{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "In a vacuum, the mass line shape of the decaying into dileptons is represented by a relativistic Breit-Wigner function, f BW (M).",
    "Within a hot QCD medium, this line shape is modified, multiplied by the Boltzmann factor, e -M∕T, to account for phase space effects [263].",
    "Fur- thermore, if is completely dissolved in the medium, its mass spectral structure spreads out and approaches a smooth distribution similar to the dielectron continuum from QGP thermal radiation, described by M 3∕2 e -M∕T [253].",
    "Figure 32 illustrates temperatures derived from BES-I dielectron data as a function of the baryon chemical potential B.",
    "The chemical freeze-out temperature T ch and B are determined by applying statistical thermal models to the yields of hadron production."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Within a hot QCD medium, this line shape is modified, multiplied by the Boltzmann factor, e -M∕T, to account for phase space effects [263].",
